title: Patched (YC S24) Is Hiring SWEs in Singapore
description: Article URL: https://www.ycombinator.com/companies/patched/jobs/hgDeMBr-software-engineer Comments URL: https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=44176314 Points: 0 # Comments: 0
author: rohansood15
excerpt: We’re looking for a high-energy, resourceful engineer to join our team as we make AI agents production-ready via incredible product design and hardcore engineering. In this role, you’ll work with a high degree of autonomy to create accurate, reliable, and secure AI agents using the best models, tooling, and frameworks out there. There are no hard requirements for this role. We’re looking for an exceptional software engineer who: Has embraced an AI-native development workflow Has a proven ability to build and launch products Can communicate clearly and enjoys working with a strong team Has a strong work ethic To apply, include a 1-minute video link introducing yourself and talking about one thing that you’re passionate about. Applications without a video link (or an AI-generated one) will not be shortlisted. We look forward to talking to you.
text: Open-source workflow automation for dev teamsSoftware Engineer$60K - $100K / 0.25% - 0.50%ExperienceAny (new grads ok)VisaUS citizenship/visa not requiredConnect directly with founders of the best YC-funded startups.Apply to role ›Rohan SoodCo-Founder and CEOAbout the roleWe’re looking for a high-energy, resourceful engineer to join our team as we make AI agents production-ready via incredible product design and hardcore engineering. In this role, you’ll work with a high degree of autonomy to create accurate, reliable, and secure AI agents using the best models, tooling, and frameworks out there. There are no hard requirements for this role. We’re looking for an exceptional software engineer who: Has embraced an AI-native development workflow Has a proven ability to build and launch products Can communicate clearly and enjoys working with a strong team Has a strong work ethic To apply, include a 1-minute video link introducing yourself and talking about one thing that you’re passionate about. Applications without a video link (or an AI-generated one) will not be shortlisted. We look forward to talking to you. About the interviewTwo Rounds of interviews: Initial Screening for 30 mins Deep-dive with live coding using AI-assisted tools for 90-120 mins About PatchedPatched is building open-source AI agents for enterprise engineering and ops teams. We believe open-source is the future of AI, and is the best way to solve AI adoption challenges, which largely stem from a lack of trust and transparency. We have just landed our first few enterprise clients and are aggressively iterating with them to build out our product. make AI agents production-ready via incredible product design and hardcore engineering.</p>
<p>In this role, you’ll work with a high degree of autonomy to create accurate, reliable, and secure AI agents using the best models, tooling, and frameworks out there.</p>
<p>There are no hard requirements for this role. We’re looking for an exceptional software engineer who:</p>
<ul>
<li>Has embraced an AI-native development workflow</li>
<li>Has a proven ability to build and launch products</li>
<li>Can communicate clearly and enjoys working with a strong team</li>
<li>Has a strong work ethic</li>
</ul>
<p>To apply, include a 1-minute video link introducing yourself and talking about one thing that you’re passionate about. Applications without a video link (or an AI-generated one) will not be shortlisted.</p>
<p>We look forward to talking to you.</p>
</div><h2>About the interview</h2><div><p>Two Rounds of interviews:</p>
<ol>
<li>Initial Screening for 30 mins</li>
<li>Deep-dive with live coding using AI-assisted tools for 90-120 mins</li>
</ol>
</div><h2>About Patched</h2><div><p>Patched is building open-source AI agents for enterprise engineering and ops teams. We believe open-source is the future of AI, and is the best way to solve AI adoption challenges, which largely stem from a lack of trust and transparency.</p>
